much joy over the years.

596
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,250
(STRUMMING)

597
00:39:38,253 --> 00:39:39,503
(SOBBING)

598
00:39:42,382 --> 00:39:43,512
God!

599
00:39:48,221 --> 00:39:49,511
Eliza.

600
00:39:54,602 --> 00:39:56,022
Eliza.

601
00:39:56,604 --> 00:39:57,614
Stop!

602
00:39:58,231 --> 00:40:00,151
Stop your wailing!

603
00:40:02,485 --> 00:40:04,065
If you let yourself be overcome

604
00:40:04,154 --> 00:40:05,494
by sorrow, you will drown in it.

605
00:40:05,613 --> 00:40:07,413
Have you stopped crying
for your children?

606
00:40:09,242 --> 00:40:12,662
You make no sounds,
but will you ever let them go in your heart?

607
00:40:17,208 --> 00:40:18,958
They are as my flesh.

608
00:40:19,085 --> 00:40:21,125
Then who is distressed?

609
00:40:21,713 --> 00:40:24,093
Do I upset the master and the mistress?

610
00:40:24,215 --> 00:40:26,545
Do you care less about my loss
than their well-being?

611
00:40:26,676 --> 00:40:28,086
Master Ford is a decent man.

612
00:40:28,219 --> 00:40:29,389
He is a slaver!

613
00:40:29,471 --> 00:40:30,391
Under the circumstances.

614
00:40:30,513 --> 00:40:32,393
Under the circumstances,
he is a slaver.

615
00:40:32,599 --> 00:40:34,559
But you truckle at his boot.

616
00:40:34,684 --> 00:40:36,394
You luxuriate in his favor.

617
00:40:36,478 --> 00:40:38,268
I survive!

618
00:40:38,396 --> 00:40:40,436
I will not fall into despair!

619
00:40:40,565 --> 00:40:42,565
I will offer up my talents to Master Ford!

620
00:40:42,692 --> 00:40:45,492
I will keep myself hearty
until freedom is opportune!

621
