shall be beaten with many stripes.

789
00:55:24,240 --> 00:55:28,080
Now, "many" signifies a great many.

790
00:55:28,495 --> 00:55:32,415
40, 100, 150 lashes.

791
00:55:37,045 --> 00:55:38,545
That's scripture.

792
00:55:39,339 --> 00:55:41,049
(WOMAN HUMMING)

793
00:55:41,966 --> 00:55:43,506
(ALL HUMMING)

794
00:55:55,063 --> 00:55:56,483
EDWARD: Pick that cotton.

795
00:55:56,606 --> 00:55:57,516
Move along, now.

796
00:55:57,607 --> 00:55:58,567
(WHIP CRACKS)

797
00:56:00,735 --> 00:56:03,655
TREACH: Come on, Edward!
Drive them niggers!

798
00:56:03,988 --> 00:56:06,988
Pick that cotton! Move along, now.

799
00:56:07,575 --> 00:56:09,535
TREACH: What are you doing, boy?
Come on!

800
00:56:12,414 --> 00:56:14,544
TREACH: 240 for Bob.

801
00:56:15,083 --> 00:56:17,043
EPPS: What
you got for James?

802
00:56:17,419 --> 00:56:19,499
295 pounds.

803
00:56:19,629 --> 00:56:22,719
That's real good, boy. That's real good.

804
00:56:23,383 --> 00:56:25,473
182 for Platt.

805
00:56:27,220 --> 00:56:30,060
How much can even
an average nigger pick a day?

806
00:56:30,223 --> 00:56:31,433
200 pounds.

807
00:56:31,558 --> 00:56:33,478
This nigger ain't even average.

808
00:56:35,311 --> 00:56:37,521
512 pounds for Patsey.

809
00:56:37,647 --> 00:56:40,397
512!

810
00:56:41,359 --> 00:56:45,359
You menfolk got no shame
letting Patsey out-pick you.

811
00:56:47,032 --> 00:56:50,452
The day ain't yet come
she swung lower than 500 pounds.

812
00:56:53,747 --> 00:56:56,247
Queen of the fields, she is.

813
00:56:56,374 --> 00:56:57,424
TREACH: 138 pounds--

814
00:56:57,542 --> 00:56:59,382
I ain't done, Treach.

815
00:57:00,128 --> 00:57:03,628
Ain't I owed a minute to
luxuriate on the work Patsey done?

816
00:57:04,257 --> 00:57:05,377
Yes, sir.

817
00:57:09,512 --> 00:57:11,222
Damn queen.

818
00:57:12,599 --> 00:57:15,559
Born and bred to the field.

819
00:57:17,228 --> 00:57:19,518
A nigger among niggers.

820
00:57:21,566 --> 00:57:23,566
And God gave her to me.

821
00:57:27,739 --> 00:57:30,659
A lesson in the rewards
of righteous living.

822
00:57:32,619 --> 00:57:34,999
All be observant to that.

823
00:57:36,081 --> 00:57:38,041
All!

824
00:57:38,708 --> 00:57:41,338
Now, Treach. Now speak.

825
00:57:42,045 --> 00:57:45,045
138 pounds for Phebe.

826
00:57:45,632 --> 00:57:48,722
Hit 145 yesterday. Pull her out.

827
00:57:49,594 --> 00:57:51,604
206 pounds for George.

828
00:57:52,097 --> 00:57:54,057
How much he pick yesterday?

829
00:57:55,058 --> 00:57:56,478
229.

830
00:57:56,601 --> 00:57:57,731
Get him out.

831
00:57:58,061 --> 00:57:59,401
Come on, get.

832
00:58:01,398 --> 00:58:02,728
Come on.

833
00:58:03,066 --> 00:58:04,686
EPPS: Come on, boy, move!

834
00:58:10,407 --> 00:58:11,617
(WHIP CRACKING)

835
00:58:11,700 --> 00:58:12,370
(MAN GROANING)

836
00:58:12,450 --> 00:58:13,120
(WOMAN GROANING)

837
00:58:25,547 --> 00:58:27,047
(HUMMING)

838
00:59:45,960 --> 00:59:47,210
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

839
00:59:47,587 --> 00:59:49,047
(DOOR OPENS)

840
00:59:49,255 --> 00:59:51,045
(SINGING)

841
00:59:53,051 --> 00:59:54,051
Get up!

842
00:59:54,177 --> 00:59:55,507
We dance tonight! Get up!

843
00:59:55,637 --> 00:59:57,217
Get your fiddle, Platt. Get up!

844
00:59:57,389 --> 00:59:59,429
Come on! Get, get, get!

845
00:59:59,557 --> 01:00:01,427
Come on, Platt. Come on!

846
01:00:01,685 --> 01:00:03,225
(UPBEAT FIDDLE MUSIC PLAYING)

847
01:00:03,269 --> 01:00:04,479
(EPPS CLAPPING)

848
01:00:13,238 --> 01:00:16,238
Come on,
where's your merriment? Move your feet!

849
01:00:28,086 --> 01:00:28,956
(GROANS)

850
01:00:29,045 --> 01:00:29,955
(MUSIC STOPS)

851
01:00:30,213 --> 01:00:30,593
MISTRESS EPPS: Sell her.

852
01:00:30,714 --> 01:00:31,344
(PATSEY SOBBING)

853
01:00:31,464 --> 01:00:32,474
EPPS: What's all this?

854
01:00:32,590 --> 01:00:35,220
You will sell the negress.

855
01:00:35,343 --> 01:00:37,143
Sell little Pats?

856
01:00:37,262 --> 01:00:40,062
She pick with more vigor
than any other nigger.

857
01:00:40,390 --> 01:00:41,220
Choose another to go.

858
01:00:41,349 --> 01:00:43,059
No other.

859
01:00:43,184 --> 01:00:44,394
Sell her.

860
01:00:44,728 --> 01:00:46,228
I will not.

861
01:00:47,397 --> 01:00:50,397
You will remove
that black bitch from this property...

862
01:00:50,525 --> 01:00:53,485
or I'll take myself back to Cheneyville.

863
01:00:54,487 --> 01:00:56,067
(SOBBING CONTINUES)

864
01:00:57,240 --> 01:00:59,490
Back to that hog's trough
where I found you?

865
01:01:02,537 --> 01:01:06,367
Do not set yourself up
against Patsey, my dear.

866
01:01:10,378 --> 01:01:12,208
Because I will rid myself of you

867
01:01:12,339 --> 01:01:14,219
well before
I do away with her.

868
01:01:22,557 --> 01:01:23,557
What you looking at?

869
01:01:25,018 --> 01:01:26,558
Damn woman.

870
01:01:27,395 --> 01:01:29,435
I won't have
my mood spoiled.

871
01:01:29,981 --> 01:01:31,651
I will not.

872
01:01:33,151 --> 01:01:33,401
Dance.

873
01:01:33,485 --> 01:01:33,735
(MUSIC RESUMES)

874
01:01:34,235 --> 01:01:35,025
Dance, I says!

875
01:01:35,111 --> 01:01:35,741
(GROANING)

876
01:01:40,408 --> 01:01:41,988
Come on!

877
01:01:42,077 --> 01:01:45,247
Pick it up, Platt.
Play that fiddle, boy.

878
01:01:45,413 --> 01:01:46,413
(EPPS WHOOPING)

879
01:01:55,215 --> 01:01:56,545
(BLOWING)

880
01:02:22,033 --> 01:02:23,083
MISTRESS EPPS: Platt.

881
01:02:25,036 --> 01:02:26,406
Yes, Mistress?

882
01:02:28,415 --> 01:02:31,035
Can you find your
way to Bartholomew's?

883
01:02:31,501 --> 01:02:32,711
I can, ma'am.

884
01:02:33,253 --> 01:02:35,053
This is a list of
goods and sundries.

885
01:02:35,213 --> 01:02:38,093
You will take it
to be filled and return immediately.

886
01:02:38,216 --> 01:02:40,426
Take your tag.

887
01:02:40,552 --> 01:02:42,392
Tell Bartholomew to add it to our debt.

888
01:02:42,554 --> 01:02:43,564
Yes, Mistress.

889
01:02:45,640 --> 01:02:47,730
Where you from, Platt?

890
01:02:50,061 --> 01:02:51,231
I told you.

891
01:02:51,396 --> 01:02:53,186
Tell me again.

892
01:02:53,606 --> 01:02:54,606
Washington.

893
01:02:54,733 --> 01:02:55,733
Who were your master?

894
01:02:56,026 --> 01:02:56,986
Master name a Freeman.

895
01:02:57,068 --> 01:02:58,738
Was he a learned man?

896
01:02:59,571 --> 01:03:01,281
I suppose so.

897
01:03:01,406 --> 01:03:02,986
He learn you to read?

898
01:03:04,743 --> 01:03:07,043
A word, here or there.

899
01:03:07,495 --> 01:03:08,995
But I have no understanding of the written--

900
01:03:09,122 --> 01:03:11,252
Don't trouble yourself with it.

901
01:03:11,624 --> 01:03:15,214
Same as the rest.
Master brought you here to work, that's all.

902
01:03:16,379 --> 01:03:19,089
Any more will earn you 100 lashes.

903
01:04:06,721 --> 01:04:08,391
(PANTING)

904
01:04:17,691 --> 01:04:19,231
(DOG WHIMPERING)

905
01:04:25,115 --> 01:04:26,065
Come here, boy.

906
01:04:29,119 --> 01:04:30,409
Come on.

907
01:04:46,469 --> 01:04:48,219
Where you going, boy?

908
01:04:48,388 --> 01:04:50,968
On my way to Bartholomew's.

909
01:04:51,099 --> 01:04:53,309
Sent by Mistress Epps.

910
01:04:57,147 --> 01:04:59,107
You best get there, then.

911
01:05:00,191 --> 01:05:01,691
Get there quick.

912
01:05:15,040 --> 01:05:16,330
(MEN CHOKING)

913
01:05:16,374 --> 01:05:17,714
(DOG BARKING)

914
01:05:30,555 --> 01:05:32,305
(SHOPKEEPER MUTTERING)

915
01:05:50,700 --> 01:05:52,200
Any trouble?

916
01:05:52,327 --> 01:05:54,697
No, ma'am. No trouble.

917
01:06:42,585 --> 01:06:44,205
(PANTING)

918
01:06:53,471 --> 01:06:55,221
Platt Epps, good Sunday morning.

919
01:06:55,390 --> 01:06:56,600
Good morning, Master Shaw.

920
01:06:56,725 --> 01:06:59,305
Master sent me to retrieve Patsey.
May I approach?

921
01:06:59,436 --> 01:07:00,596
You may.

922
01:07:02,147 --> 01:07:03,607
(PANTING)

923
01:07:05,108 --> 01:07:06,228
(WOMEN LAUGHING)

924
01:07:11,239 --> 01:07:12,739
Excuse me, Mistress Shaw.

925
01:07:13,283 --> 01:07:14,583
Nigger Platt.

926
01:07:14,701 --> 01:07:16,491
Patsey, Master wishes you to return.

927
01:07:16,619 --> 01:07:18,369
The Sabbath day, I is free to roam.

928
01:07:18,663 --> 01:07:21,463
Master sent me running to fetch you,
said no time should be wasted.

929
01:07:21,624 --> 01:07:23,384
Drink of tea?

930
01:07:23,460 --> 01:07:25,380
Thank you, Mistress, but I don't dare.

931
01:07:25,503 --> 01:07:27,553
Would you know of
Master Epps's consternation...

932
01:07:27,672 --> 01:07:30,972
to be any lessened with your timely return?

933
01:07:31,551 --> 01:07:33,971
Anger's his constant condition.

934
01:07:34,054 --> 01:07:34,724
Sit.

935
01:07:35,472 --> 01:07:37,562
Sit and drink the tea that I offered.

936
01:07:42,604 --> 01:07:44,984
What'n be Epps's concern?

937
01:07:45,023 --> 01:07:46,233
(SIGHS)

938
01:07:46,608 --> 01:07:48,398
I'd rather not say.

939
01:07:49,069 --> 01:07:53,239
Oh, little gossip on the Sabbath be fine.
All things in moderation.

940
01:07:55,075 --> 01:07:57,075
As you are aware...

941
01:07:57,243 --> 01:08:03,213
Master Epps is a man of hard countenance.

942
01:08:03,458 --> 01:08:05,538
You know he has ill feeling
towards your husband.

943
01:08:05,710 --> 01:08:07,090
He do.

944
01:08:08,046 --> 01:08:10,086
Master Epps has somehow
come to believe...

945
01:08:10,215 --> 01:08:14,215
that Master Shaw
is something of a lothario.

946
01:08:15,720 --> 01:08:18,260
A misguided belief, no doubt.

947
01:08:18,390 --> 01:08:19,560
No doubt...

948
01:08:19,683 --> 01:08:21,983
if not born out of truth itself.

949
01:08:24,187 --> 01:08:25,647
I meant no disrespect.

950
01:08:26,189 --> 01:08:28,019
He ain't heard you.

951
01:08:28,316 --> 01:08:30,526
SOLOMON: I meant
no disrespect to you, Mistress.

952
01:08:30,568 --> 01:08:32,108
(LAUGHS)

953
01:08:33,488 --> 01:08:37,158
Got no cause to worry for my sensibilities.

954
01:08:37,992 --> 01:08:42,412
I ain't felt the end
of a lash in more years I can recall.

955
01:08:42,580 --> 01:08:44,580
I ain't worked a field, neither.

956
01:08:45,291 --> 01:08:47,131
Where once I served...

957
01:08:47,252 --> 01:08:50,212
now, I have
others serving me.

958
01:08:50,714 --> 01:08:53,384
The cost to
my current existence...

959
01:08:53,508 --> 01:08:56,588
be Master Shaw
broadcasting his affections...

960
01:08:56,970 --> 01:08:59,600
and me enjoying
the pantomime of his fidelity.

961
01:09:01,182 --> 01:09:05,482
If that what keep me from
cotton picking niggers, that what it be.

962
01:09:05,603 --> 01:09:09,403
A small and reasonable price
to be paid, for sure.

963
01:09:13,987 --> 01:09:16,407
I know what it like to be the object

964
01:09:16,531 --> 01:09:19,201
of Master's predilections and peculiarities.

965
01:09:20,326 --> 01:09:23,036
A lusty visit in the night...

966
01:09:23,163 --> 01:09:25,503
or a visitation with the whip.

967
01:09:27,000 --> 01:09:28,420
Take comfort, Patsey.

968
01:09:28,626 --> 01:09:30,706
The good Lord will manage Epps.

969
01:09:31,296 --> 01:09:35,716
In His own time,
the good Lord will manage them all.

970
01:09:36,176 --> 01:09:39,386
The curse of the pharaohs
were a poor example...

971
01:09:39,512 --> 01:09:42,432
of what wait for the plantation class.

972
01:09:47,979 --> 01:09:49,519
This is nice.

973
01:10:00,992 --> 01:10:03,412
EPPS: Pats. Patsey!

974
01:10:03,578 --> 01:10:05,288
Do not look in his direction. Continue on.

975
01:10:05,997 --> 01:10:07,537
-Patsey!
-Found her, Master.

976
01:10:08,166 --> 01:10:10,376
And brought her back, just as instructed.

977
01:10:13,046 --> 01:10:15,166
What did you just now tell her?

978
01:10:15,298 --> 01:10:17,048
What did you say to Pats?

979
01:10:18,176 --> 01:10:19,966
No words were spoken,
none of consequence.

980
01:10:21,596 --> 01:10:23,256
You're a liar.

981
01:10:23,556 --> 01:10:25,476
You damn liar.

982
01:10:26,309 --> 01:10:28,559
I saw you talking with her.

983
01:10:29,521 --> 01:10:31,151
Tell me.

984
01:10:32,607 --> 01:10:34,397
I cannot speak of what did not occur.

985
01:10:34,651 --> 01:10:36,441
I'll cut your black throat!

986
01:10:36,569 --> 01:10:37,699
Master!

987
01:10:38,321 --> 01:10:39,661
You come here.

988
01:10:40,156 --> 01:10:41,236
-Master Epps.
-I said come here!

989
01:10:41,408 --> 01:10:42,278
I brought her back, just like you--

990
01:10:44,202 --> 01:10:45,582
-Come here!
-Master!

991
01:10:47,747 --> 01:10:48,747
Master.

992
01:10:51,418 --> 01:10:53,588
I got her, just as instructed.

993
01:10:55,130 --> 01:10:56,130
Master Epps!

994
01:10:56,381 --> 01:10:57,971
You stay away from Pats, boy.

995
01:10:59,592 --> 01:11:01,222
(PIGS SQUEALING)

996
01:11:04,222 --> 01:11:05,472
Master Epps.

997
01:11:07,142 --> 01:11:08,232
(GROANS)

998
01:11:18,570 --> 01:11:20,070
(LAUGHING)

999
01:11:21,531 --> 01:11:22,661
(PANTING)

1000
01:11:26,077 --> 01:11:27,367
(CONTINUES LAUGHING)

1001
01:11:32,292 --> 01:11:34,212
It's the Lord's day.

1002
01:11:35,545 --> 01:11:38,465
Ain't nothing Christian
in us carrying on like this.

1003
01:11:39,007 --> 01:11:40,467
(PANTING)

1004
01:11:45,430 --> 01:11:46,970
I concede to you.

1005
01:11:49,559 --> 01:11:50,979
In the name of valor...

1006
01:11:52,520 --> 01:11:53,690
help your master to his feet.

1007
01:11:58,443 --> 01:11:59,533
I'm gonna kill you!

1008
01:12:00,111 --> 01:12:01,571
MISTRESS EPPS: What's the fuss?

1009
01:12:01,738 --> 01:12:03,448
Master Epps believed Patsey and me

1010
01:12:03,573 --> 01:12:05,283
to be in conversation when we were not.

1011
01:12:05,408 --> 01:12:06,618
I tried to explain, but it's led to all this.

1012
01:12:06,993 --> 01:12:07,623
What is it?

1013
01:12:08,203 --> 01:12:11,083
You can't remain
the Sabbath without her under your eye?

1014
01:12:11,206 --> 01:12:12,956
You are a no-account bastard.

1015
01:12:13,041 --> 01:12:15,041
A filthy, godless heathen.

1016
01:12:15,168 --> 01:12:17,668
My bed is too holy for you to share.

1017
01:12:18,004 --> 01:12:19,054
What's he been telling you?

1018
01:12:19,214 --> 01:12:20,474
Of your misbegotten ways.

1019
01:12:20,590 --> 01:12:22,590
And he would know what of anything?

1020
01:12:23,718 --> 01:12:25,598
I ain't even spoken with him today.

1021
01:12:26,429 --> 01:12:28,389
You lying nigger, Platt.

1022
01:12:29,057 --> 01:12:30,137
Have I?

1023
01:12:32,435 --> 01:12:33,595
Have I?

1024
01:12:36,272 --> 01:12:38,612
There. There's all the truth he got.

1025
01:12:39,609 --> 01:12:41,029
Damn nigger.

1026
01:13:58,063 --> 01:13:59,113
(GRUNTS)

1027
01:14:07,197 --> 01:14:08,487
(PANTING)

1028
01:14:15,246 --> 01:14:16,366
(GRUNTS)

1029
01:14:20,377 --> 01:14:21,957
(PANTING)

1030
01:14:32,722 --> 01:14:34,102
Patsey.

1031
01:14:40,063 --> 01:14:41,363
(CHOKING)

1032
01:14:52,492 --> 01:14:54,452
(GASPING)

1033
01:16:02,979 --> 01:16:04,399
(UPBEAT FIDDLE MUSIC PLAYING)

1034
01:16:30,965 --> 01:16:33,295
MISTRESS EPPS: A moment
from the dancing.

1035
01:16:34,427 --> 01:16:36,597
Come sample what I baked for y'all.

1036
01:16:36,971 --> 01:16:39,561
MEN: Thank you, Mistress.

1037
01:16:39,599 --> 01:16:40,599
WOMEN: Thank you, Mistress.

1038
01:16:40,725 --> 01:16:43,055
There will be none for you, Patsey.

1039
01:16:44,396 --> 01:16:46,016
You see that?

1040
01:16:46,356 --> 01:16:49,146
You see that look
of insolence she give me?

1041
01:16:50,068 --> 01:16:51,398
I seen nothing but her turn away.

1042
01:16:51,569 --> 01:16:53,739
Are you blind or ignorant?

1043
01:16:54,072 --> 01:16:56,282
It was hot, hateful scorn.

1044
01:16:56,408 --> 01:16:58,488
It filled that black face.

1045
01:16:59,160 --> 01:17:00,330
You tell me you didn't see it...

1046
01:17:00,453 --> 01:17:04,463
it's because you choose not to look,
or are you saying I lie?

1047
01:17:04,582 --> 01:17:07,042
Whatever it was, it passed.

1048
01:17:07,585 --> 01:17:10,375
Is that how you are with the niggers?

1049
01:17:11,047 --> 01:17:14,217
Letting every ill thought fester inside them?

1050
01:17:15,010 --> 01:17:16,390
Look at them.

1051
01:17:16,469 --> 01:17:18,599
They foul with it.

1052
01:17:18,972 --> 01:17:21,022
They foul with their hate.

1053
01:17:21,599 --> 01:17:25,599
You let it be, it's gonna come
back to us in the dark of night.

1054
01:17:25,979 --> 01:17:27,399
You want that?

1055
01:17:28,148 --> 01:17:30,728
You want them black animals leave us

1056
01:17:31,026 --> 01:17:33,566
gut like pigs in our own sleep?

1057
01:17:34,070 --> 01:17:35,200
Oh...

1058
01:17:35,697 --> 01:17:39,077
You are manless.

1059
01:17:39,242 --> 01:17:41,752
A damn eunuch if there ever was.

1060
01:17:42,412 --> 01:17:44,292
If you won't stand for me, I pray you'd

1061
01:17:44,414 --> 01:17:46,214
at least be a credit to your own kind...

1062
01:17:46,374 --> 01:17:48,504
and beat every foul thought from them.

1063
01:17:57,218 --> 01:17:58,508
(SCREAMING)

1064
01:17:59,054 --> 01:18:00,064
Beat it from them!

1065
01:18:04,601 --> 01:18:06,231
(PATSEY WHIMPERING)

1066
01:18:17,280 --> 01:18:18,110
MISTRESS EPPS: Eat.

1067
01:18:19,366 --> 01:18:21,076
Fill yourselves.

1068
01:18:21,659 --> 01:18:23,079
And then we dance.

1069
01:18:28,291 --> 01:18:30,251
I said, eat.

1070
01:18:35,423 --> 01:18:37,133
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1071
01:18:45,975 --> 01:18:46,345
Platt.

1072
01:18:46,434 --> 01:18:46,984
(GASPS)

1073
01:18:48,561 --> 01:18:50,061
Platt, you awake?

1074
01:18:53,733 --> 01:18:54,733
I am.

1075
01:18:56,069 --> 01:18:58,239
I have a request.

1076
01:18:58,613 --> 01:19:00,743
An act of kindness.

1077
01:19:04,244 --> 01:19:07,004
I secreted it from the mistress.

1078
01:19:08,540 --> 01:19:09,330
Return it.

1079
01:19:09,457 --> 01:19:11,167
It yours, Platt.

1080
01:19:12,460 --> 01:19:14,170
For what cause?

1081
01:19:14,295 --> 01:19:18,425
All I ask, end my life.

1082
01:19:19,592 --> 01:19:22,972
Take my body to the margin of the swamp.

1083
01:19:23,096 --> 01:19:26,096
Take me by the throat,
hold me low in the water...

1084
01:19:26,224 --> 01:19:28,984
until I is still and without life.

1085
01:19:29,436 --> 01:19:31,226
Bury me in a lonely place of dying.

1086
01:19:31,396 --> 01:19:33,226
I will do no such thing.

1087
01:19:34,399 --> 01:19:36,229
The gory detail with which you speak...

1088
01:19:36,359 --> 01:19:38,739
I thought on it long and hard.

1089
01:19:40,238 --> 01:19:42,198
It is melancholia.

1090
01:19:42,657 --> 01:19:44,237
Nothing more.

1091
01:19:45,410 --> 01:19:48,250
How can you fall into such despair?

1092
01:19:48,413 --> 01:19:51,373
How can you not know?

1093
01:19:53,460 --> 01:19:57,460
I ain't got no comfort in this life.

1094
01:19:59,716 --> 01:20:03,716
If I can't buy mercy from you...

1095
01:20:04,054 --> 01:20:06,104
I'll beg it.

1096
01:20:06,222 --> 01:20:07,722
There are others.

1097
01:20:08,975 --> 01:20:10,305
-Beg them.
-I'm begging you.

1098
01:20:10,435 --> 01:20:11,595
Why?

1099
01:20:12,312 --> 01:20:16,192
Why would you consign me to
damnation with such an ungodly request?

1100
01:20:16,316 --> 01:20:18,356
There is God here!

1101
01:20:19,194 --> 01:20:22,534
God is merciful...

1102
01:20:22,655 --> 01:20:25,405
and he forgive merciful acts.

1103
01:20:25,658 --> 01:20:28,238
Won't be no hell for you.

1104
01:20:30,372 --> 01:20:31,542
Do it.

1105
01:20:36,586 --> 01:20:39,586
Do what I ain't
got the strength to do myself.

1106
01:21:19,170 --> 01:21:20,960
EPPS: <i>It's a plague.</i>

1107
01:21:21,965 --> 01:21:23,005
TREACH: <i>It's cotton worm.</i>

1108
01:21:23,133 --> 01:21:25,973
<i>It's a plague. It's damn biblical.</i>

1109
01:21:27,137 --> 01:21:30,017
<i>Two seasons God done
sent a plague to smite me.</i>

1110
01:21:32,392 --> 01:21:35,982
<i>What I done that God hates me so?</i>

1111
01:21:42,068 --> 01:21:44,238
It's that godless lot.

1112
01:21:46,156 --> 01:21:48,026
They brought this on me.

1113
01:21:48,158 --> 01:21:50,408
I bring them God's word and heathens

1114
01:21:50,493 --> 01:21:52,703
