1122
01:22:43,088 --> 01:22:44,088
Listen up.

1123
01:22:44,631 --> 01:22:46,551
You're Judge Turner's for the season.

1124
01:22:46,633 --> 01:22:48,513
More, if need be, until my crops return.

1125
01:22:49,302 --> 01:22:51,602
Y'all bring no disrespect to me.

1126
01:22:51,721 --> 01:22:54,641
Don't bring no
biblical plagues to him, you hear?

1127
01:22:54,974 --> 01:22:57,064
Or I'll take it out on your skin.

1128
01:22:58,061 --> 01:22:59,401
Get out.

1129
01:23:51,406 --> 01:23:53,236
Get off the porch.
You ain't supposed to be on the porch.

1130
01:23:53,366 --> 01:23:54,576
Get off the porch.

1131
01:24:01,374 --> 01:24:02,634
Platt, is it?

1132
01:24:03,209 --> 01:24:04,249
Yes, sir.

1133
01:24:04,377 --> 01:24:07,377
You cultivate cane previously?

1134
01:24:08,006 --> 01:24:09,126
No, sir, I have not.

1135
01:24:09,257 --> 01:24:11,377
It comes to you quite naturally.

1136
01:24:11,551 --> 01:24:12,551
Are you educated?

1137
01:24:13,219 --> 01:24:16,559
No, sir.
Niggers are hired to work, not read or write.

1138
01:24:18,433 --> 01:24:20,103
You play the fiddle.

1139
01:24:20,518 --> 01:24:22,398
Yes, sir. Yes, I do.

1140
01:24:23,646 --> 01:24:25,976
Willard Yarner, a planter up the bayou...

1141
01:24:26,107 --> 01:24:29,397
celebrates his anniversary
in three weeks' time.

1142
01:24:29,486 --> 01:24:31,736
I'll hold out your name to him.

1143
01:24:32,072 --> 01:24:34,492
What you earn is yours to keep.

1144
01:24:35,241 --> 01:24:36,331
Yes, sir.

1145
