1475
01:48:59,748 --> 01:49:02,078
Strike the life from her.

1476
01:49:08,256 --> 01:49:09,586
Beat her.

1477
01:49:11,343 --> 01:49:13,513
Give her the whip! Give it all to her!

1478
01:49:14,971 --> 01:49:17,721
Platt, you come here and you beat her now.

1479
01:49:20,268 --> 01:49:21,388
Platt!

1480
01:49:24,230 --> 01:49:25,400
Come here!

1481
01:49:27,233 --> 01:49:29,363
PATSEY: I'd rather it you, Platt!

1482
01:49:30,320 --> 01:49:32,070
You strike her.

1483
01:49:32,989 --> 01:49:34,369
Strike her.

1484
01:49:35,617 --> 01:49:37,367
(PATSEY CONTINUES SOBBING)

1485
01:49:48,463 --> 01:49:50,013
(PATSEY YELLS)

1486
01:49:51,716 --> 01:49:53,176
(PATSEY GROANING)

1487
01:49:56,554 --> 01:49:58,224
He pantomimes.

1488
01:49:58,723 --> 01:50:01,233
There's barely a welt on her.

1489
01:50:01,601 --> 01:50:04,101
That's what your niggers make of you...

1490
01:50:04,229 --> 01:50:06,399
a fool for the taking.

1491
01:50:10,985 --> 01:50:13,355
EPPS: Strike her, Platt.
Strike her!

1492
01:50:14,572 --> 01:50:15,702
(GROANING)

1493
01:50:30,046 --> 01:50:31,416
You will strike her.

1494
01:50:31,548 --> 01:50:33,338
You will strike her until her flesh

1495
01:50:33,425 --> 01:50:35,215
is rent and meat and blood flow equal...

1496
01:50:35,343 --> 01:50:38,143
or I will kill every nigger in my sight.

1497
01:50:38,263 --> 01:50:39,683
You understand me?

1498
01:50:40,015 --> 01:50:42,725
Strike her! Strike her!

1499
01:50:53,361 --> 01:50:54,701
(PATSEY SCREAMS)

1500
01:50:57,991 --> 01:50:59,491
(PATSEY SOBBING)

1501
01:51:20,388 --> 01:51:22,018
(COUGHING)

1502
01:51:26,102 --> 01:51:28,982
EPPS: Until I say no more.
I ain't said nothing!

1503
01:51:38,698 --> 01:51:40,118
Give me the whip!

1504
01:51:41,117 --> 01:51:42,287
Get up!

1505
01:51:46,664 --> 01:51:48,214
(PATSEY SCREAMING)

1506
01:52:01,680 --> 01:52:03,390
Thou devil!

1507
01:52:06,059 --> 01:52:07,479
Sooner or later...

1508
01:52:08,228 --> 01:52:10,688
somewhere in the course of eternal

1509
01:52:10,980 --> 01:52:13,480
justice, thou shalt answer for this sin!

1510
01:52:14,651 --> 01:52:16,241
(PANTING)

1511
01:52:18,988 --> 01:52:22,078
Sin? There is no sin.

1512
01:52:23,410 --> 01:52:26,370
Man does how he pleases
with his property.

1513
01:52:32,043 --> 01:52:35,593
At the moment, Platt,
I'm of great pleasure.

1514
01:52:35,714 --> 01:52:37,594
You be goddamn
careful I don't want to

1515
01:52:37,716 --> 01:52:39,546
come and lighten
my mood no further.

1516
01:53:11,374 --> 01:53:12,544
(GASPS)

1517
01:53:12,709 --> 01:53:14,209
(WHIMPERING)

1518
01:53:19,049 --> 01:53:20,219
(SHOUTS)

1519
01:53:20,717 --> 01:53:22,137
(SOBBING)

1520
01:53:35,482 --> 01:53:37,402
(GASPING IN PAIN)

1521
01:53:48,119 --> 01:53:50,409
(SOBBING)

1522
01:54:57,981 --> 01:54:59,401
Master Bass.

1523
01:54:59,607 --> 01:55:02,987
I want to ask you what part
of the country you come from.

1524
01:55:04,195 --> 01:55:06,065
No part of this land.

1525
01:55:07,115 --> 01:55:09,195
I originate
from Canada.

1526
01:55:10,201 --> 01:55:11,621
Now, guess where that is.

1527
01:55:11,745 --> 01:55:13,655
I know where Canada is.

1528
01:55:14,539 --> 01:55:16,329
I've been there myself.

1529
01:55:21,212 --> 01:55:23,092
Montreal...

1530
01:55:23,214 --> 01:55:26,264
and Kingston and Queenston
and a great many places.

1531
01:55:26,384 --> 01:55:28,264
Well-traveled for a slave.

1532
01:55:28,386 --> 01:55:29,466
How came you here?

1533
01:55:31,514 --> 01:55:33,224
Master Bass...

1534
01:55:35,518 --> 01:55:39,058
if justice had been done,
I never would have been here.

1535
01:55:43,651 --> 01:55:45,111
How's this?

1536
01:55:46,196 --> 01:55:47,236
Tell me all.

1537
01:55:52,577 --> 01:55:54,747
I'm afraid to tell you.

1538
01:55:56,414 --> 01:55:59,504
Every word you speak
is a profound secret.

1539
01:56:07,217 --> 01:56:08,967
Your story...

1540
01:56:09,469 --> 01:56:11,049
it is amazing.

1541
01:56:11,179 --> 01:56:13,179
And in no good way.

1542
01:56:15,266 --> 01:56:16,476
(SIGHS)

1543
01:56:17,977 --> 01:56:21,477
Do you believe, sir, in justice, as you said?

1544
01:56:22,607 --> 01:56:24,227
I do.

1545
01:56:24,401 --> 01:56:28,241
That slavery is an evil
that should befall none?

1546
01:56:31,074 --> 01:56:32,744
I believe so.

1547
01:56:33,076 --> 01:56:34,986
If you truly do...

1548
01:56:36,621 --> 01:56:39,621
then I ask, I beg...

1549
01:56:42,377 --> 01:56:45,207
that you write my friends in the north...

1550
01:56:45,505 --> 01:56:48,375
acquainting them of my situation...

1551
01:56:49,634 --> 01:56:54,064
and beseeching them
to forward free papers.

1552
01:56:59,060 --> 01:57:00,600
It would be...

1553
01:57:03,648 --> 01:57:06,528
an unspeakable happiness...

1554
01:57:08,236 --> 01:57:10,276
to see my wife...

1555
01:57:12,657 --> 01:57:15,077
and my family again.

1556
01:57:20,957 --> 01:57:24,287
I traveled this country
for the best part of 20 years...

1557
01:57:25,045 --> 01:57:27,955
and my freedom is everything.

1558
01:57:28,048 --> 01:57:32,388
The fact that I can walk out of here
tomorrow brings me great pleasure.

1559
01:57:35,055 --> 01:57:37,265
My life doesn't mean much to anyone.

1560
01:57:38,516 --> 01:57:42,226
It seems yours might mean
a lot to a whole lot of people.

1561
01:57:44,064 --> 01:57:48,444
But what you ask of me, sir, scares me.

1562
01:57:50,570 --> 01:57:53,450
And I must say, I am afraid.

1563
01:57:54,574 --> 01:57:56,994
Not just for you, but for me.

1564
01:58:06,211 --> 01:58:08,301
I will write your letter, sir.

1565
01:58:08,963 --> 01:58:10,053
And if it brings you your freedom,

1566
01:58:10,131 --> 01:58:11,221
it will be more than a pleasure.

1567
01:58:11,383 --> 01:58:13,343
It will have been my duty.

1568
01:58:13,468 --> 01:58:16,428
Now, would you kindly
